<response><error><![CDATA[OK]]></error><limit>1</limit><offset>0</offset><number_of_page_results>1</number_of_page_results><number_of_total_results>1</number_of_total_results><status_code>1</status_code><results><aliases/><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/character/3005-379/]]></api_detail_url><birthday/><date_added>2008-06-08 21:35:33</date_added><date_last_updated>2011-05-05 12:20:00</date_last_updated><deck><![CDATA[Darrius is a playable character in the Mortal Kombat series of games.]]></deck><description><![CDATA[<h2>Profile</h2> <b>Alignment:</b> Neutral<br/> <b>Species:</b> Seidan<br/> <b>Origin:</b> <a data-ref-id="3035-618" href="/orderrealm/3035-618/" slug="orderrealm">      Orderrealm</a><br/> <b>Allies:</b> <a data-ref-id="3005-378" href="/dairou/3005-378/" slug="dairou">      Dairou</a><br/> <b>Enemies:</b> <a data-ref-id="3005-384" href="/hotaru/3005-384/" slug="hotaru">      Hotaru</a><br/><br/><h2>Story</h2>Darrius is an enemy and revolutionary in the Realm of Order. Considered a terrorist by some, he sees himself as an enemy of the establishment and leader of  a resistance movement to overthrow the powers currently in place. He is willing to go to great lengths to bring about the downfall of the <a data-ref-id="3035-618" href="/orderrealm/3035-618/" slug="orderrealm">      Orderrealm</a>, which includes strategic assassinations and manipulation to gain recruits to his cause.  In his plot to assassinate <a data-ref-id="3005-384" href="/hotaru/3005-384/" slug="hotaru">      Hotaru</a>, he killed the family of <a data-ref-id="3005-378" href="/dairou/3005-378/" slug="dairou">      Dairou</a>. He lays the blame for this act squarely on Hotaru and successfully gained Dairou as an ally. Darrius then sent him on a mission to kill Hotaru, but the outcome is never made clear.<br/> <br/><h2>Endings</h2><h3><a data-ref-id="3030-6421" href="/mortal-kombat-4/3030-6421/" slug="mortal-kombat-4"> <b> Mortal Kombat 4 </b></a></h3>Darrius manages to steal a prized document of the Seidan government and goes to battle against Hotaru. Despite a costly battle, Darrius and his resistance manage to defeat Hotaru and his men, thus gaining control of the government. <br/> <br/><h3><a data-ref-id="3030-11843" href="/mortal-kombat-armageddon/3030-11843/" slug="mortal-kombat-armageddon"> <b>Mortal Kombat: Armageddon </b></a></h3>After defeating Blaze, Darrius is given access to the treasure and power that was intended for <a data-ref-id="3005-409" href="/taven/3005-409/" slug="taven">     Taven</a> and <a data-ref-id="3005-377" href="/daegon/3005-377/" slug="daegon">    Daego</a><a data-ref-id="3005-377" href="/daegon/3005-377/" slug="daegon">   n</a>. Though he is finally able to defeat Hotaru using these artifacts, Taven and Daegon are then sent on a quest to defeat Darrius retrieve what is rightfully theirs.<br/><br/><h2>Appearances</h2><h3>Deception</h3>Darrius's Fighting Styles are Shinto Ryu and Leopard. Darrius's Weapon Style is Gauntlets. <br/><br/><h3>Armageddon</h3>Darrius's Fighting Styles is Goju Ryu and his Weapons are Gauntlets.<br/><br/><br/><h2>Costume<br/></h2>According to <a data-ref-id="3040-11101" href="/steve-beran/3040-11101/" slug="steve-beran">      Steve Beran</a>, <i>"The original intention was to make Darrius the new leader of the Red Dragon."<br/>"He has an imposing physical presence and a ''take no B.S.'' attitude, like a star athlete who had made his way to fame from a rough upbringing and humble beginnings. His look was inspired by the comic book art of the 60's and 70's; the end result was intended to be a mixture of those elements fused with a sleek modern approach." </i><br/><br/><br/><h2>Special Moves</h2><h3><figure data-align="right" data-embed-type="image" data-img-src="http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/0/7661/635799-cutout.png" data-ref-id="1300-635799" data-resize-url="" data-resized="" data-size="small"><a href="http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/0/7661/635799-cutout.png" data-ref-id="1300-635799"><img src="http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/7661/635799-cutout.png"></a><figcaption>Dangerously good looking</figcaption></figure></h3> <h3>Deception</h3><ul class="plain-list"><li>Tricky Blast: B, F, LP</li> <li>Twisty Kick : B, F, LK</li> <li>Chest Cruncher : B, F, HP</li> <li>Target Practice : D, F, HK</li> </ul> <br/><br/><h2>Fatalities</h2><h3>Deception</h3><ul class="plain-list"><li>Arm Rip: (Sweep distance) U, D, B, F, HK</li> <li>Rearrange: (Close) D, F, F, U, HP</li> <li>Hara-Kiri: B, F, F, LP</li></ul>]]></description><gender>1</gender><id>379</id><image><icon_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_avatar/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></icon_url><medium_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></medium_url><screen_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/screen_medium/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></screen_url><small_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></small_url><super_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_large/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></super_url><thumb_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_avatar/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></thumb_url><tiny_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_mini/8/87790/1539909-darrius_bio.png]]></tiny_url></image><last_name/><name><![CDATA[Darrius]]></name><real_name/><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/darrius/3005-379/]]></site_detail_url><first_appeared_in_game><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/game/3030-383/]]></api_detail_url><id>383</id><name><![CDATA[Mortal Kombat: Deception]]></name></first_appeared_in_game><concepts><concept><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/concept/3015-21/]]></api_detail_url><id>21</id><name><![CDATA[Finishing Move]]></name><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/finishin